Author-Name: Rodrigo R. Soares 
Author-Name: Bruno L. S. Falcão 
Title: The Demographic Transition and the Sexual Division of Labor 
Abstract:
 This paper presents a theory in which increases in female labor force
 participation and reductions in the gender-wage gap are generated as part
 of a single process of demographic transition, initially characterized by
 reductions in mortality and fertility. The paper suggests a relationship
 between gains in life expectancy and changes in the role of women in
 society that has not been identified before in the literature. Mortality
 reductions affect the incentives of individuals to invest in human capital
 and to have children, with implications for female labor force
 participation and the wage differential between men and women. The paper
 also presents some empirical evidence to support the predictions of the
 theory. (c) 2008 by The University of Chicago. All rights reserved. 
