Author-Name: Markus Goldstein 
Author-Name: Christopher Udry 
Title: The Profits of Power: Land Rights and Agricultural Investment in Ghana 
Abstract:
 We examine the impact of ambiguous and contested land rights on investment
 and productivity in agriculture in Akwapim, Ghana. We show that
 individuals who hold powerful positions in a local political hierarchy
 have more secure tenure rights and that as a consequence they invest more
 in land fertility and have substantially higher output. The intensity of
 investments on different plots cultivated by a given individual
 corresponds to that individual's security of tenure over those specific
 plots and, in turn, to the individual's position in the political
 hierarchy relevant to those specific plots. (c) 2008 by The University of Chicago. All rights reserved. 
